        },
        {
          "id": "dw70",
          "type": "text",
          "content": "The morning light filters through\nthe blinds, soft and unassuming.\nI lie still for a few minutes,\nlistening to the birds.",
          "x": 486,
          "y": 178,
          "width": 318,
          "height": 90,
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width-height",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#F0E6C8",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "lineHeight": 1.75
        },
        {
          "id": "dw71",
          "type": "text",
          "content": "There is something about Sundays\nthat asks you to slow down. Not\nout of laziness — but reverence.",
          "x": 486,
          "y": 276,
          "width": 318,
          "height": 68,
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width-height",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#F0E6C8",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "lineHeight": 1.75
        },
        {
          "id": "dw72",
          "type": "text",
          "content": "I made coffee slowly. Poured it\ninto the old ceramic mug. Sat by\nthe window and watched the street.",
          "x": 486,
          "y": 352,
          "width": 318,
          "height": 68,
          "textGrowth": "fixed-width-height",
          "fontSize": 14,
          "fontWeight": "400",
          "fill": "#F0E6C8",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "lineHeight": 1.75
        },
